main event: A possible satellite observed from Ewa Beach, Hawaii on January 27, 1965.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for approximately 1 minute,The object appeared brighter than stars, similar in brightness to the moon,The object reportedly disappeared and reappeared repeatedly, indicating it was climbing,The object exhibited maneuvers similar to a visible satellite,The conclusion of the report was that it was an astronomical observation classified as a meteor.
sighted object: one bright object in the sky
witness description: 25 year old male from Ewa Beach, Honolulu
